    "problemStatement": "You are given two integers N&nbsp;(N\u22652)N \\ ( N \\geq 2)N&nbsp;(N\u22652) and SSS. You have to construct an array AAA containing NNN integers such that:\n\n\n0\u2264Ai\u2264S0 \\leq A_i \\leq S0\u2264Ai\u200b\u2264S for each 1\u2264i\u2264N1 \\leq i \\leq N1\u2264i\u2264N\nA1+A2+\u2026+AN=SA_1 + A_2 + \\ldots + A_N = SA1\u200b+A2\u200b+\u2026+AN\u200b=S\nA1&amp;A2&amp;\u2026&amp;AN=0A_1 \\mathbin{\\&amp;} A_2 \\mathbin{\\&amp;} \\ldots \\mathbin{\\&amp;} A_N = 0A1\u200b&amp;A2\u200b&amp;\u2026&amp;AN\u200b=0, where &amp;\\mathbin{\\&amp;}&amp; denotes bitwise AND operator.\nThe maximum element of the array is minimized.\nFind the maximum element of the array AAA.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line of input will contain a single integer TTT, denoting the number of test cases.\nThe first and only line of each test case contains two space-separated integers NNN and SSS \u2014 the length of array and sum of array elements respectively.\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output on a new line the maximum element of the array AAA.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u22641041 \\leq T \\leq 10^41\u2264T\u2264104",
      "2\u2264N\u22641092 \\leq N \\leq 10^92\u2264N\u2264109",
      "1\u2264S\u22641091 \\leq S \\leq 10^91\u2264S\u2264109"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "",
    "outputFormat": "",
    "sampleTestCases": [
      {
        "id": "sample_1",
        "input": "4\n2 7\n3 6\n5 21\n100 256455",
        "output": "4\n3\n5\n2570",
        "explanation": "Explanation:\nTest case 111: One possible array is A=[4,3]A = [4,3]A=[4,3]. Here 4+3=74 +3=74+3=7 and 4&3=04 \\mathbin{\\&} 3=04&3=0.\nTest case 222: One possible array is [1,2,3][1, 2, 3][1,2,3]. Here 1+2+3=61+2+3=61+2+3=6 and 1&2&3=01 \\mathbin{\\&} 2 \\mathbin{\\&} 3=01&2&3=0.\nTest case 333: One possible array is [2,4,5,5,5][2, 4, 5,5,5][2,4,5,5,5]. Here 2+4+5+5+5=212+4+5+5+5=212+4+5+5+5=21 and 2&4&5&5&5=02 \\mathbin{\\&} 4 \\mathbin{\\&} 5 \\mathbin{\\&} 5 \\mathbin{\\&} 5=02&4&5&5&5=0."
      }
